Ugandan Ministers Resign Over Corruption Allegations, TV Says

-- B y   F r e d   O j a m b o
-- 
2011-10-12T16:31:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-12/ugandan-ministers-resign-over-corruption-allegations-tv-says.html
Three Ugandan ministers resigned
today to pave way for an investigation after they were named by
a parliament probe into government procurements as the nation
prepared to host the commonwealth heads of government meeting in
November 2007, state-owned television reported, without saying
where it got the information.  Foreign Affairs Minister Sam Kutesa, Government Chief whip
John Nasasira and Mwesigwa Rukutana, minister of state for
labor, resigned so that the investigation can take ,’’ Uganda
Broadcasting Corporation said. The ministers say they are
innocent, the broadcaster said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
